<%- title 'How to install user scripts' %>
<%- description 'Describes how to install user scripts from Greasy Fork.' %>

<p>How you install user scripts depends on which browser you use. Typically, you will need to install a browser extension. This is not an exhaustive list, please <%=link_to 'contact us', help_contact_path%> if you have any additions.</p>

<p>Once user scripts are enabled in your browser, it should be as simple as clicking the "Install" button on any script's page on Greasy Fork.</p>

<h2>Firefox</h2>
<ul>
	<li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/greasemonkey/">Greasemonkey</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/scriptish/">Scriptish</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>Google Chrome</h2>
<ul>
